f: \mathbb{Z} \times \mathbb{Z} \to \mathbb{Z}
(x,y) \in \mathbb{Z} \times \mathbb{Z}
f(x,y) = ax + by
a
b
\alpha\in\mathbb Z
\beta\in \mathbb Z
1=\alpha a+\beta b
z\in \mathbb Z
z=z\alpha a+z\beta b = f(z\alpha,z\beta)
f:A\to B
b \in B
a \in A
f(a) = b
z \in \mathbb{Z}
(x,y) \in \mathbb{Z \times Z}
 f(x,y) = z \implies ax + by = z 
